						<p>Slab (No. 2) forming part of the roof of a dolmen near the Chauḍēśvarī temple in a field to the west of the village.</p>						

						<p>Circa 9th century.</p>						

						<p>This fragmentary record refers to a gift of land situated below a tank. All other details are lost.</p>						

